Dear all,

This is to announce the availability of a preprint
"Connections and path connections in groupoids".

Abstract:

We describe two gauge theoretic notions of connection in a
(differentiable) groupoid. The two notions are related via the notion
of holonomy. Holonomy formation (integration) is shown to be inverse
of a certain differentiation process.
The method is that of Synthetic Differential Geometry, notably in the
form of "First Neighbourhood of the Diagonal".

The preprint can be dowlnoaded from

http://www.imf.au.dk/publs?id=619

or from my home page

http://home.imf.au.dk/kock/

Yours
Anders


